                            <comment id="13854038" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Fri, 20 Dec 2013 15:13:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried to keep this down, but over time I&apos;ve come to think it makes less and less sense. The benefits are not worth the initial experience for those that don&apos;t have things setup and running in a fast environment. The cost of an expiration can be quite high as well, and increases as your index size increases, as it can easily trigger replication recoveries.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
